thing about it. Which means that it’s siloed and has to be; Microsoft proved
that back in 2007 when its heroic attempt to unsilo consumer platform development
squeezed out Vista, a day (by which I mean years) late and a dollar (by which
I mean billions) short.  If Android’s going to be great, Android has to care
about being Android.") (p nil "And I care about Android, because it’s a really good way to have the
