useful indicator of which way the market’s heading.") (img ((src . "DSCF2742.png") (alt . "Hawaiian vegetation, partially sunlit"))) (h2 ((id . "p-2")) "What I Saw") (p nil "This is uncontrolled anecdotal scavenging, not real data collection. But still:") (ul nil (li nil (p nil "Astonishingly few point-&-shoots.")) (li nil (p nil "A huge number of iPhones and Androids (more of the former, but plenty
of both).")) (li nil (p nil "Unsurprisingly many big honking CaNikon SLRs.")) (li nil (p nil "Surprisingly, a waterproof compact or two at most pools and beaches.")) (li nil (p nil "Memorably, a few iPads, held up to shoot Mom & Sis in front of the 
waterfall or whatever. The photographer looks dorky but I don’t think cares
because you preview and shoot at the same time, if it weren’t that awkward
it’d sweep the planet, but it is that awkward.")) (li nil (p nil "And then, in the places where photos matter, compacts.  Lots of
compacts; maybe as many as SLRs. Panasonics and Sonys mostly; I had the only
Fujifilm I saw but it got called out by savvy-seeming photogs carrying way
heavier metal.  I kept having to say “No, it’s not an X100.”"))) (img ((src . "DSCF2786.png") (alt . "A stone personage in the waves"))) (div ((class . "caption")) (p nil "Look closely, there’s a creature in that stone.")) (h2 ((id . "p-3")) "Instinct Call") (p nil "I can’t encourage you, honestly, to trust mine. But it’s shouting in my
ear, saying the future is electronic viewfinders and small bodies.") (p nil "SLRs are really hard to shrink
because of their lens legacy and prism-size requirements, neither of which get
help from Moore’s Law.  
The mirrorlesses are doing all sorts of innovation in sensors and lenses
and ergonomics, and their viewfinder systems are going to improve every year
because they " (em nil "are") " in Moore’s-Law territory.") (p nil "And also, once again " (em nil "size matters") ". The whole point of a camera is
that, to be useful, it has to go with you.  The lighter and smaller it is, the
more likely it is to be there.") (p nil "The corollary, of course, is that more and more photography is going to
happen through mobile phones because they’re the most likely to be there.  So
cameras have to find the sweet spot, where they take significantly better
pictures than phones, but aren’t so bulky they get left behind.") (p nil "Is my new Fujifilm X-E1 a complete replacement for the Pentax SLRs I’ve been
carrying around for years?  Not entirely, because I don’t have a lens longer
than 55mm, and really no urge to get one, because once you get up into the big
lenses, you’re kind of trading off portability anyhow.") (p nil "But for tourism, particularly if there’s some
" (a ((href . "/ongoing/When/201x/2013/03/26/Finite-Integral-of-the-Earth")) "serious
walking") " involved, the Fuji trumps the Pentax, big-time; the image quality
is about as good, the ergonomics are mostly better, and the size decides
it.") (h2 ((id . "p-1")) "Just Getting into Photography?") (p nil "Go mirrorless. Don’t even think about an SLR.  It’s a no-brainer."))))) ("Finite Surface Integral of the Earth" "(div ((xmlns . \"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\")) (p nil \"I have watched the piecewise creation of the world; new pieces
